customLabels.label: Here are a few things you'll need to complete your template configuration:
customLabels.name: WhatYouWillNeedInfo

customLabels.label: You’ll copy and paste anchor text into your files to dynamically insert Salesforce data and DocuSign fields.
customLabels.name: WhatYouWillNeedStep1Info

customLabels.label: You’ll need to have at least one Salesforce data source and the fields you want to add to your document.
customLabels.name: WhatYouWillNeedStep2Info

customLabels.label: You can also add DocuSign fields, such as signature or date signed into your Word templates.
customLabels.name: WhatYouWillNeedStep3Info

customLabels.label:
Select your main data source

Select the data source where your users will begin generating documents. For example, if you choose Opportunity, users can pull data from an Opportunity and related objects, like Account.
customLabels.name: StartingObjectGuidance1

customLabels.label:
Need Help?

Find out more about template configurations in the DocuSign Support Center.
customLabels.name: StartingObjectGuidance3

customLabels.label:
Add Salesforce fields

Salesforce fields allow you to dynamically populate information on your document directly from Salesforce. For example, if you selected Account as your main data source, you may want to pull Account Name or Billing Address. Be sure to copy and paste the corresponding anchor text into your Word templates. Decide formatting and conditional options in the dropdown menu.
customLabels.name: MergeFieldsGuidance1

customLabels.label:
Add DocuSign fields

You can also have DocuSign fields, like signature, automatically prepared for recipients. Be sure to copy and paste the corresponding anchor text into your Word templates.
customLabels.name: MergeFieldsGuidance2

customLabels.label:
Upload Word templates

Upload all of the Word templates for this configuration. For each template, you can choose a suffix option for generated documents. You can also decide if users should generate a Word document or a PDF.
customLabels.name: ImportTemplatesGuidance1

customLabels.label:
Determine bulk document creation option

If you’ve uploaded multiple Word templates with this configuration, you can choose if all documents should be generated every time. By default, users can select which ones they want to generate. However, if your users need to generate all documents, then select Bulk Document Creation.
customLabels.name: ImportTemplatesGuidance2

customLabels.label:
Test your templates

Choose data sources from Salesforce and click Preview to generate example documents.
customLabels.name: PreviewGuidance1

customLabels.label:
Review and update

Check your documents in Word to confirm text placement and formatting.You can update your templates by going back to any previous step in this configuration wizard without losing your progress.
customLabels.name: PreviewGuidance2

customLabels.label:
Determine your button label

Give your button a descriptive label, such as Generate Sales Order.
customLabels.name: PublishGuidance1

customLabels.label:
Select page layouts and deployment option

Decide where your button should appear and select to deploy as a Detail Page Button (Salesforce Classic) or Quick Action (Lightning Experience). If you don’t want a button on any layout, deselect all layout options before clicking Create Button. Your button will be available in the Salesforce Object Manager setup.
customLabels.name: PublishGuidance2

customLabels.label: What is DocuSign CLM for Salesforce?
customLabels.name: WhatIsDocuSign

customLabels.label: It's an app that connects your Salesforce data with DocuSign CLM. This lets you use your Salesforce data to create business documents. DocuSign CLM for Salesforce lets you store and manage those documents.
customLabels.name: WhatIsDocuSignAns

customLabels.label: Why should I use DocuSign CLM for Salesforce?
customLabels.name: WhyDocuSignAgreements

customLabels.label: DocuSign CLM for Salesforce uses your Salesforce Data to generate documents. This speeds up document generation and removes the possibility of human error.
customLabels.name: WhyDocuSignAns

customLabels.label: How does DocuSign CLM for Salesforce speed up my document generation process?
customLabels.name: DocumentGenerationProcess

customLabels.label: You can generate documents by pressing a single button in Salesforce. To do this, you'll have to create a custom button on your object page layouts.
customLabels.name: DocumentGenerationAns

customLabels.label: Why should I use this app instead of storing my documents in Salesforce?
customLabels.name: WhyOnlyDocuSign

customLabels.label: If you store documents in Salesforce they aren't organized and are hard to access. That slows down reviews, workflows and getting signatures. DocuSign CLM for Salesforce keeps things organized for you. It organizes documents automatically, even when you generate new documents. Plus, you can access your documents directly from Salesforce.
customLabels.name: WhyOnlyDocuSignAns

customLabels.label: DocuSign CLM is the secure cloud app for DocuSign CLM for Salesforce. It lets you generate documents, collaborate with stakeholders and automate your processes. DocuSign CLM for Salesforce connects DocuSign CLM with your Salesforce org.
customLabels.name: WhatIsDocuSignCLMAns

customLabels.label: How do I install DocuSign CLM for Salesforce?
customLabels.name: InstallDocuSignAgreements

customLabels.label: First, go to the Salesforce AppExchange. Then search for the DocuSign Apps Launcher and follow the installation steps. You'll need to be a Salesforce administrator to do this.
customLabels.name: InstallAgreementsAns

customLabels.label: How do I authenticate DocuSign CLM for Salesforce?
customLabels.name: AuthenticateAgreements

customLabels.label: Open the DocuSign Apps Launcher in Salesforce after installation. Then sign in with your DocuSign CLM-enabled DocuSign login credentials and follow the the prompts to establish the reverse connection with your Salesforce credentials. This enables integration between the two systems.
customLabels.name: AuthenticateAgreementsAns

customLabels.label: Admins are users with special privileges and responsibilities in DocuSign CLM for Salesforce. Admins can map objects and manage users.
customLabels.name: WhatIsAnAdminAns

customLabels.label: How do Admins add and manage users?
customLabels.name: HowAdminManageUsers

customLabels.label: Admins can add or manage users from the User Management page.
customLabels.name: HowAdminManageUsersAns

customLabels.label: Do I have to pay extra fees per-user after installing the app?
customLabels.name: InstallationFees

customLabels.label: No. The fees displayed on the AppExchange page show the general cost per-user if they purchased a DocuSign CLM package. There are no extra costs associated with installing any DocuSign apps.
customLabels.name: InstallationFeesAns

customLabels.label: Why should I configure a layout?
customLabels.name: WhyConfigureLayout

customLabels.label: Configuring a layout will let you see your object folders in Salesforce and DocuSign CLM. This will then let you use your DocuSign CLM files and folders on your linked object pages.
customLabels.name: WhyConfigureLayoutAns

customLabels.label: What happens after I've mapped an object?
customLabels.name: AfterMappingObject

customLabels.label: DocuSign CLM for Salesforce adds the object's data to your Visualforce library. To see the object's folders and files, you'll need to add them to any relevant Salesforce page layouts.
customLabels.name: AfterMappingObjectAns

customLabels.label: Why can't I see my object folder?
customLabels.name: CannotSeeObjectFolder

customLabels.label: If you're not seeing mapped objects, you likely need to edit your page layouts in Salesforce. You'll need to be a Salesforce Administrator to do this.
customLabels.name: CannotSeeObjectFolderAns

customLabels.label: What are Salesforce objects and fields?
customLabels.name: SalesforceObjectsFields

customLabels.label: Salesforce objects are how Salesforce stores data. Every object has several associated fields containing data. To use objects and fields in DocuSign CLM for Salesforce, you'll first need to map your objects.
customLabels.name: SalesforceObjectsFieldsAns

customLabels.label: Object mapping is the process of connecting objects from your Salesforce org to DocuSign CLM. The DocuSign Apps Launcher setup walks you through the steps.
customLabels.name: WhatIsObjMappingAns

customLabels.label: Why should I map my Salesforce objects?
customLabels.name: WhyToMapObject

customLabels.label: DocuSign CLM for Salesforce needs the data in your objects to generate documents. Mapping your Salesforce objects is how you give access to that data. Only DocuSign CLM for Salesforce admins can map objects.
customLabels.name: WhyToMapObjectAns

customLabels.label: How do I map an Object?
customLabels.name: HowToMapObject

customLabels.label: To map your Salesforce objects, navigate to the CLM Integration page. Then select "Map New". Follow the prompts to complete setup.
customLabels.name: HowToMapObjectAns

customLabels.label: You can edit or remove mapped objects from the CLM Integration page. Removing the object will mean you no longer can use the object's data for document generation.
customLabels.name: RemoveMappedObjectAns

customLabels.label: Are there any standard objects I should map?
customLabels.name: MappingStandardObjects

customLabels.label: Every business is different and has different needs. "Account" and "Opportunity" are examples of standard objects that many businesses will use. DocuSign CLM for Salesforce maps those objects by default.
customLabels.name: MappingStandardObjectsAns

customLabels.label: You can map custom Salesforce objects. To use custom objects you'll need to have created them in Salesforce first.
customLabels.name: MappingCustomObjectsAns

customLabels.label: What should I name my Custom Object Folders?
customLabels.name: CustomObjectFolder

customLabels.label: Naming conventions are set by the object's merge fields. This process starts when you map your Salesforce objects. These folders' names will update whenever the contents of the fields change.
customLabels.name: CustomObjectFolderAns

customLabels.label: Why can't I just type in a name for my Custom Object Folders?
customLabels.name: TypeFolderName

customLabels.label: If you type in a name for those folders, then every instance of that object will have the same folder name. Salesforce doesn't allow duplicate folder names. That's why we recommend selecting a field instead.
customLabels.name: TypeFolderNameAns

customLabels.label: Why do I need to choose a location for my object folder?
customLabels.name: NeedObjectFolderLocation

customLabels.label: Choosing a location for your object folder keeps your documents organized.
customLabels.name: NeedObjectFolderLocationAns
